item.title: My routers username or password is different how do i find it?
item.dc:creator: @Dark_Iz_Fire Dark Iz Fire
item.description:
@Dark_Iz_Fire wrote:

You have to type your default gateway ip address on your internet explorer then a box will pop-up asking for your username and password…to find your ip address Open your cmd by going to Start > Run > cmd.
Type in ipconfig´ It will say your default gateway, so type that in your browser and you will get a login screen. Skip the username part and fill inadmin´ at the password field or type in admin as username and password as password

Credit to God of Ikiliki for tut
